.SH DownContFilterMA
Compute the minimum\-amplitude downward continuation filter of Wieczorek
and Phillips (1998).
.SH Usage
\f[CR]wl\f[R] = DownContFilterMA (\f[CR]l\f[R], \f[CR]half\f[R],
\f[CR]r\f[R], \f[CR]d\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]wl\f[R] : output, real(dp)
The amplitude of the downward continuation filter.
.TP
\f[CR]l\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The spherical harmonic degree.
.TP
\f[CR]half\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The spherical harmonic degree where the filter is equal to 0.5.
.TP
\f[CR]r\f[R] : input, real(dp)
The reference radius of the gravitational field.
.TP
\f[CR]d\f[R] : input, real(dp)
The radius of the surface to downward continue to.
.SH Description
\f[CR]DownContFilterMA\f[R] will calculate the downward continuation
filter of Wieczorek and Phillips (1998; eq.
19) for a given spherical harmonic degree \f[CR]l\f[R].
The input parameters include \f[CR]half\f[R], which is the degree where
the filter is equal to 0.5, and \f[CR]r\f[R] and \f[CR]d\f[R], which are
the reference radius of the gravitational field and the radius of the
surface to downward continue to, respectively.
.SH References
Wieczorek, M. A. and R. J. Phillips, Potential anomalies on a sphere:
applications to the thickness of the lunar crust, J. Geophys.
Res., 103, 1715\-1724, 1998.
